{"title":"Canyon Torque:ON massive travel e-MTB: Everything you need to know","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/02/02/canyon-torqueon-massive-travel-e-mtb-everything-you-need-to-know/","date":1612263611000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p><span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-box-3\"></span>The Torque:ON has joined Canyon’s roster of e-MTBs as a 175mm travel gravity-focused machine. Taking the progressive geometry of the Torque further, this 27.5″ bike is possibly the most aggressive e-MTB we’ve seen yet. Pricing of the Canyon Torque:ON starts at €4,499; let’s take a look at what you’re getting for your money.</p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-freeride-bike-park-ebike.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-freeride-bike-park-ebike.jpg\" alt=\"canyon torque:on e-mtb whip\" width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-freeride-bike-park-ebike.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-freeride-bike-park-ebike.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-freeride-bike-park-ebike-297x167.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-freeride-bike-park-ebike-800x450.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-freeride-bike-park-ebike-120x68.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-freeride-bike-park-ebike-768x432.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-freeride-bike-park-ebike-696x392.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-freeride-bike-park-ebike-1068x601.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-freeride-bike-park-ebike-747x420.jpg 747w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-freeride-bike-park-ebike.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-freeride-bike-park-ebike-297x167.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-freeride-bike-park-ebike-800x450.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-freeride-bike-park-ebike-120x68.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-freeride-bike-park-ebike-768x432.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-freeride-bike-park-ebike-696x392.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-freeride-bike-park-ebike-1068x601.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-freeride-bike-park-ebike-747x420.jpg 747w\"></a></p><ul><li>Intention: Park e-MTB / Freeride e-MTB</li><li>Fork Travel: 180mm</li><li>Rear Wheel Travel: 175mm</li><li>Wheel Size: 27.5″</li><li>Motor: Shimano EP8</li><li>Starting Price: € 4,499</li><li>Sizes: S, M, L, XL</li></ul><figure id=\"attachment_250801\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-250801\"><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-8-emtb.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-8-emtb.jpg\" alt=\"The Canyon Torque:ON 8 freeride-eMTB\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-8-emtb.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-8-emtb.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-8-emtb-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-8-emtb-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-8-emtb-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-8-emtb-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-8-emtb-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-8-emtb-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-8-emtb-630x420.jpg 630w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-8-emtb.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-8-emtb-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-8-emtb-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-8-emtb-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-8-emtb-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-8-emtb-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-8-emtb-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-8-emtb-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-250801\">The Canyon Torque:ON 8 freeride-eMTB with RockShox ZEB R fork and Super Deluxe Select R shock</figcaption></figure><p>The Canyon Torque:ON is offered in two models, both rocking a full aluminium frame with air shocks delivering 175mm of rear wheel travel. A Shimano EP8 motor gives 85Nm of Torque powered by a downtube-integrated 504Wh battery.</p><p>That seems a little under-gunned, right? Especially when you consider that the 2021 Spectral:ON gets a 630Wh battery. Canyon say there was nothing really stopping them from putting a bigger battery into the Torque:ON… just ride quality.<span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-medrectangle-3\"></span></p><figure id=\"attachment_250802\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-250802\"><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-shimano-ep8-motor.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-shimano-ep8-motor.jpg\" alt=\"canyon torque:on emtb shimano ep8 motor 85Nm torque 504Wh battery\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-shimano-ep8-motor.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-shimano-ep8-motor.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-shimano-ep8-motor-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-shimano-ep8-motor-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-shimano-ep8-motor-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-shimano-ep8-motor-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-shimano-ep8-motor-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-shimano-ep8-motor-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-shimano-ep8-motor-630x420.jpg 630w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-shimano-ep8-motor.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-shimano-ep8-motor-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-shimano-ep8-motor-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-shimano-ep8-motor-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-shimano-ep8-motor-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-shimano-ep8-motor-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-shimano-ep8-motor-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-shimano-ep8-motor-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-250802\">All Canyon Torque:ON frame sizes allow space for a water bottle inside the front triangle</figcaption></figure><p>The intention with the Canyon Torque:ON was to produce a gravity-capable bike for bike park laps and steep freeride terrain. Seemingly though, they wanted more than just a long travel bike with a motor and battery whacked on it. Canyon say the Torque:ON is a very playful bike, and the decision to opt for the 504Wh battery was key to that, offering a ~1kg weight advantage over the 630Wh.&nbsp;</p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-8-rockshox-zeb-fork.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-8-rockshox-zeb-fork.jpg\" alt=\"canyon torque:on 8 alloy long travel emtb\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-8-rockshox-zeb-fork.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-8-rockshox-zeb-fork.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-8-rockshox-zeb-fork-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-8-rockshox-zeb-fork-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-8-rockshox-zeb-fork-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-8-rockshox-zeb-fork-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-8-rockshox-zeb-fork-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-8-rockshox-zeb-fork-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-8-rockshox-zeb-fork-630x420.jpg 630w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-8-rockshox-zeb-fork.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-8-rockshox-zeb-fork-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-8-rockshox-zeb-fork-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-8-rockshox-zeb-fork-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-8-rockshox-zeb-fork-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-8-rockshox-zeb-fork-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-8-rockshox-zeb-fork-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-8-rockshox-zeb-fork-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>For riders who will spend that battery capacity twice over in a single ride, Canyon are offering a spare battery “value package” for both Torque:ON models, adding €500 to the price tag.</p><h3>Anything unusual about it?</h3><p>The Torque:ON uses Canyon’s tried-and-tested Triple Phase Kinematics, altered slightly to reduce the anti-squat.&nbsp;<em>Reduce? </em>Yes, quite the opposite to what bike designers are normally aiming for. We can explain…</p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-climbing.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-climbing.jpg\" alt=\"canyon torque:on 8 climbing steep terrain anti-squat reduced favoring reduced pedal kickback for descending\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-climbing.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-climbing.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-climbing-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-climbing-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-climbing-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-climbing-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-climbing-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-climbing-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-climbing-630x420.jpg 630w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-climbing.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-climbing-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-climbing-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-climbing-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-climbing-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-climbing-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-climbing-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-climbing-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>In brief, anti-squat is a trait of suspension design that resists the compression of the suspension caused by mass transfer during acceleration (pedaling). Anti-squat is generally a good thing as it prevents “pedal bob” associated with the uneven application of torque throughout the pedal stroke, making the bike feel more efficient when climbing steep terrain.</p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-cornering.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-cornering.jpg\" alt=\"canyon torque:on reduced pedal kickback enhanced rear wheel traction\" width=\"1200\" height=\"1043\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-cornering.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-cornering.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-cornering-297x258.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-cornering-800x695.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-cornering-120x104.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-cornering-768x668.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-cornering-696x605.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-cornering-1068x928.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-cornering-483x420.jpg 483w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-cornering.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-cornering-297x258.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-cornering-800x695.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-cornering-120x104.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-cornering-768x668.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-cornering-696x605.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-cornering-1068x928.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-cornering-483x420.jpg 483w\"></a></p><p>The presence of a motor on an e-MTB smooths out the uneven torque that is normally measurable throughout the pedal stroke, reducing the tendency of the bike to “squat” (or bob) as the rider pedals. Canyon decided to take advantage of this fact, sacrificing a little anti-squat in favor of reducing pedal kickback for improved rear wheel traction on descents.</p><p>For a more detailed explanation of <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2018/09/13/suspension-tech-what-is-anti-squat/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">anti-squat</a> and <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/09/18/aasq-85-what-is-pedal-kick-back-full-suspension-chain-growth/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">pedal kickback</a>, check out our Suspension Tech pieces in the links. I digress… back to the Torque:ON.</p><h3>Torque:ON Geometry</h3><figure id=\"attachment_250807\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-250807\"><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-green-cream.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-green-cream.jpg\" alt=\"canyon torque:on 8 rockshox spec model green cream colorway\" width=\"1200\" height=\"706\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-green-cream.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-green-cream.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-green-cream-297x175.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-green-cream-800x471.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-green-cream-120x71.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-green-cream-768x452.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-green-cream-696x409.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-green-cream-1068x628.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-green-cream-714x420.jpg 714w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-green-cream.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-green-cream-297x175.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-green-cream-800x471.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-green-cream-120x71.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-green-cream-768x452.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-green-cream-696x409.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-green-cream-1068x628.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-green-cream-714x420.jpg 714w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-250807\">The Canyon Torque:ON 8 complete bike weighs a claimed 23.74 kg</figcaption></figure><p><span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-box-4\"></span>The all-new Canyon Torque:ON shares the same suspension layout as the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/10/07/canyons-torque-and-sender-al-get-a-color-refresh-and-all-new-component-packages/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Torque</a> Enduro MTB but its geometry progresses things further. The Torque:ON is both slacker and longer than its analogue counterpart, a fact consistent across the S-XL size range. While the Torque is offered in XS, Canyon opted to drop that frame size with the e-MTB.</p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-jump-bike.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-jump-bike.jpg\" alt=\"canyon torque:on emtb jumps freeride bike\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-jump-bike.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-jump-bike.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-jump-bike-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-jump-bike-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-jump-bike-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-jump-bike-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-jump-bike-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-jump-bike-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-jump-bike-630x420.jpg 630w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-jump-bike.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-jump-bike-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-jump-bike-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-jump-bike-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-jump-bike-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-jump-bike-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-jump-bike-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/canyon-torque-on-emtb-jump-bike-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>A 180mm travel fork sits at a 63.5° head angle with the seat tube lying back at 74°. Reach spans a 435mm-510mm range with short 430mm chainstays on all frames. The BB drops 15mm with short 160mm crank arms on small and medium frames and 165mm for L &amp; XL.</p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-GEOMETRY.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-GEOMETRY.jpg\" alt=\"canyon torque:on geometry chart\" width=\"1200\" height=\"1234\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-GEOMETRY.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-GEOMETRY.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-GEOMETRY-292x300.jpg 292w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-GEOMETRY-800x823.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-GEOMETRY-117x120.jpg 117w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-GEOMETRY-768x790.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-GEOMETRY-696x716.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-GEOMETRY-1068x1098.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-GEOMETRY-408x420.jpg 408w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-GEOMETRY.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-GEOMETRY-292x300.jpg 292w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-GEOMETRY-800x823.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-GEOMETRY-117x120.jpg 117w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-GEOMETRY-768x790.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-GEOMETRY-696x716.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-GEOMETRY-1068x1098.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-GEOMETRY-408x420.jpg 408w\"></a></p><h4>Why isn’t there a 29er?</h4><p>Canyon say they wanted to keep the Torque:ON firmly in the “playful” category of e-MTBs, preferring that over the outright speed offered by 29″ wheels. The acoustic <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/10/07/canyons-torque-and-sender-al-get-a-color-refresh-and-all-new-component-packages/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Torque</a> was never offered as a 29er, and so neither is the Torque:ON.<span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-leader-1\"></span></p><h3>Updated Spectral:ON, Neuron:ON and Grand Canyon:ON</h3><figure id=\"attachment_250796\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-250796\"><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-canyon-spectral-on-shiamno-ep8-motor-update.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-canyon-spectral-on-shiamno-ep8-motor-update.jpg\" alt=\"2021 canyon spectral:on gets shaimno ep8 motor update\" width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-canyon-spectral-on-shiamno-ep8-motor-update.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-canyon-spectral-on-shiamno-ep8-motor-update.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-canyon-spectral-on-shiamno-ep8-motor-update-297x167.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-canyon-spectral-on-shiamno-ep8-motor-update-800x450.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-canyon-spectral-on-shiamno-ep8-motor-update-120x68.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-canyon-spectral-on-shiamno-ep8-motor-update-768x432.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-canyon-spectral-on-shiamno-ep8-motor-update-696x392.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-canyon-spectral-on-shiamno-ep8-motor-update-1068x601.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-canyon-spectral-on-shiamno-ep8-motor-update-747x420.jpg 747w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-canyon-spectral-on-shiamno-ep8-motor-update.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-canyon-spectral-on-shiamno-ep8-motor-update-297x167.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-canyon-spectral-on-shiamno-ep8-motor-update-800x450.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-canyon-spectral-on-shiamno-ep8-motor-update-120x68.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-canyon-spectral-on-shiamno-ep8-motor-update-768x432.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-canyon-spectral-on-shiamno-ep8-motor-update-696x392.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-canyon-spectral-on-shiamno-ep8-motor-update-1068x601.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-canyon-spectral-on-shiamno-ep8-motor-update-747x420.jpg 747w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-250796\">The 2021 Canyon Spectral: ON is updated with the Shimano EP8 drive unit and gets a bigger 630Wh battery</figcaption></figure><p>As well as the addition of the all-new Canyon Torque:ON, Canyon have updated the Grand Canyon:ON, <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/03/17/canyon-e-bikes-land-in-the-u-s-with-new-spectralon-other-countries-see-redesigned-neuronon/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Spectral:ON</a> and <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/03/17/canyon-e-bikes-land-in-the-u-s-with-new-spectralon-other-countries-see-redesigned-neuronon/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Neuron:ON</a> with Shimano’s new <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/08/31/shimano-ep8-steps-up-top-emtb-system-with-more-power-better-e-bike-integration/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">EP8 motor</a>. That replaces the 2020 bikes’ STEPS E8000 drive systems. Additionally, the 2021 Spectral:ON gets a bigger 630Wh battery. Frames and geometry are all identical to previous iterations.&nbsp;</p><h3>Pricing &amp; Availability</h3><p>Canyon will offer two Torque:ON models in all markets outside the US: the Torque:ON 8 retails at €4,499 while the Torque:ON 9 is priced at €5,799. Both versions are additionally available with a dual battery option for an extra €500.</p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-Complete-spec-list-all-models.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-Complete-spec-list-all-models.jpg\" alt=\"Canyon Troque:on complete spec list 8 9 models\" width=\"1200\" height=\"744\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-Complete-spec-list-all-models.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-Complete-spec-list-all-models.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-Complete-spec-list-all-models-297x184.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-Complete-spec-list-all-models-800x496.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-Complete-spec-list-all-models-120x74.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-Complete-spec-list-all-models-768x476.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-Complete-spec-list-all-models-696x432.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Canyon-Torque-ON-Complete-spec-list-all-models-1068x662.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/w